      "|A 32-year-old German man admitted in court on Monday that he sold t...|A 32-year-old German man admitted court Monday sold weapon used tee...|\n",
      "|After the split vote in the Iowa caucus race between Hillary Clinto...|After split vote Iowa caucus race Hillary Clinton Bernie Sanders ta...|\n",
      "|FBI Director James Comey on Thursday defended his handling of Democ...|FBI Director James Comey Thursday defended handling Democratic pres...|\n",
      "|The top Democrat in the U.S. House of Representatives said on Frida...|The top Democrat U.S. House Representatives said Friday Congress pr...|\n",
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "only showing top 5 rows\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Removing English stopwords from the \"text\" column and store the result in \"stop_text\", caching for faster reuse\n",
    "rm_stops_df = en_df.withColumn(\"stop_text\", remove_stops_udf(en_df[\"text\"])).cache()\n",
    "\n",
    "#Checking results to visualy inspect the changes between \"text\" and \"stop_text\" columns\n",
    "rm_stops_df.select(\"text\", \"stop_text\").show(5, truncate= 70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we clean the text further by removing unwanted features such as URLs, mentions, punctuation, numbers, and very short or non-alphanumeric words, as well as converts everything to lower case. We apply the **remove_features_udf** function on the \"stop_text\" column and save the cleaned output in a new column called \"feat_text\". The resulting DataFrame is cached to improve performance in subsequent operations.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 55,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
