      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "|president obama months left office stage presidency wants make sure...|President Obama months left office stage presidency, wants make sur...|\n",
      "|  year old german man admitted court monday sold weapon used teenag...|A 32-year-old German man admitted court Monday sold weapon used tee...|\n",
      "|after split vote iowa caucus race hillary clinton bernie sanders ta...|After split vote Iowa caucus race Hillary Clinton Bernie Sanders ta...|\n",
      "|fbi director james comey thursday defended handling democratic pres...|FBI Director James Comey Thursday defended handling Democratic pres...|\n",
      "|the top democrat   house representatives said friday congress promp...|The top Democrat U.S. House Representatives said Friday Congress pr...|\n",
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "only showing top 5 rows\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Cleaning \"stop_text\" by removing URLs, mentions, punctuation, numbers, and short/non-alphanumeric words, caching the result in \"feat_text\"\n",
    "rm_features_df = rm_stops_df.withColumn(\"feat_text\", remove_features_udf(rm_stops_df[\"stop_text\"])).cache()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualy inspecting changes\n",
    "rm_features_df.select(\"feat_text\",\"stop_text\").show(n=5, truncate=70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After cleaning the text, we perform part-of-speech tagging on the \"feat_text\" column using the **tag_and_remove_udf** function. This function keeps only nouns, verbs, and adjectives, helping us focus on the most meaningful words. The processed text is stored in a new column called \"tagged_text\". We cache the DataFrame in the same way as before to speed up future operations and display a sample of the cleaned and tagged text for inspection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "|                                                             feat_text|                                                           tagged_text|\n",
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "|president obama months left office stage presidency wants make sure...|president months left office stage presidency wants make sure likes...|\n",
      "|  year old german man admitted court monday sold weapon used teenag...|year old german man admitted court monday sold weapon used teenage ...|\n",
      "|after split vote iowa caucus race hillary clinton bernie sanders ta...|split vote iowa caucus race hillary clinton bernie sanders talk vot...|\n",
      "|fbi director james comey thursday defended handling democratic pres...|fbi director james comey defended handling democratic presidential ...|\n",
      "|the top democrat   house representatives said friday congress promp...|top democrat house representatives said friday congress raise feder...|\n",
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "only showing top 5 rows\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Appling POS tagging to keep only nouns, verbs, and adjectives from \"feat_text\", as well caching result in \"tagged_text\"\n",
    "tagged_df = rm_features_df.withColumn(\"tagged_text\", tag_and_remove_udf(rm_features_df[\"feat_text\"])).cache()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualy inspecting changes\n",
    "tagged_df.select(\"feat_text\",\"tagged_text\").show(n=5, truncate=70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we lemmatize the words in the \"tagged_text\" column using the **lemmatize_udf** function, which reduces words to their base or root form. This helps us in normalizing the text and improving consistency for downstream tasks. The lemmatized text then is saved in a new column called \"lemm_text\". We cache the DataFrame to again in simular manner optimize performance for further processing. Finally, we display a sample of the tagged and lemmatized text to verify the transformation."
