      "|year old german man admitted court monday sold weapon used teenage ...|year old german man admit court monday sell weapon use teenage gunm...|\n",
      "|split vote iowa caucus race hillary clinton bernie sanders talk vot...|split vote iowa caucus race hillary clinton bernie sander talk vote...|\n",
      "|fbi director james comey defended handling democratic presidential ...|fbi director james comey defend handle democratic presidential cand...|\n",
      "|top democrat house representatives said friday congress raise feder...|top democrat house representative say friday congress raise federal...|\n",
      "+----------------------------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+\n",
      "only showing top 5 rows\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Lemmatizing words in \"tagged_text\" to their root forms and store the result in \"lemm_text\", as well caching the updated DataFrame\n",
    "lemm_df = tagged_df.withColumn(\"lemm_text\", lemmatize_udf(tagged_df[\"tagged_text\"])).cache()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualy inspecting changes\n",
    "lemm_df.select(\"tagged_text\",\"lemm_text\").show(n=5, truncate=70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we create a new DataFrame final_df by selecting only the lemmatized text column (lemm_text) and the label column from the shuffled_df. Then, we rename the lemm_text column to text in the final step in our processed_df DataFrame to standardize the column name for further use, as well as dropping all the rows in \"text\" column that now are empty due to all the transformation performed.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 58,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Select only the lemmatized text and label columns from the shuffled dataframe\n",
    "final_df = lemm_df.select( lemm_df['lemm_text'], lemm_df['label'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rename the 'lemm_text' column to 'text' for consistency and ease of use in later steps\n",
    "processed_df = final_df.withColumnRenamed(\"lemm_text\", \"text\")"
   ]
