   "execution_count": 59,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Dropping rows where the \"text\" column is null, empty, or contains only whitespace after all the preprocessing\n",
    "processed_df = processed_df.filter(\n",
    "    (col(\"text\").isNotNull()) & (length(trim(col(\"text\"))) > 0)\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Also, we release the cached memory of multiple intermediate DataFrames — en_df, rm_stops_df, rm_features_df, tagged_df, and lemm_df — by calling .unpersist() on each. This helps free up system resources after these DataFrames are no longer needed for further processing."
   ]
