    "### **Loading and saving of processed_df**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We save the fully preprocessed dataset to reuse it in other notebooks, avoiding repeated heavy processing. To save the data, we use coalesce(50) to reduce the number of output files without shuffling the data. This helps preserve data order and improves performance. Using coalesce(1) would put all data in one partition, which risks high memory usage and slows down the job. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 74,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "processed_df.coalesce(50).write.csv(\"./data/processed_multi\", header=True, mode=\"overwrite\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we combine multiple csv part files, generated by Spark when saving data in multiple (20) partitions, into a single consolidated csv file. We first collect and sort all part files from the output directory. Then open the first part file to write its header and data to the final csv. For the remaining part files, we skip their headers and appends only the data rows. This results in one unified csv file with a single header, making it easier to work with it later on."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 75,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Combined CSV written to: ./data/processed_df.csv\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "csv_dir = \"./data/processed_multi\" # directory containing the our new csv part files \n",
    "output_csv = \"./data/processed_df.csv\" # path for the our combined output csv file\n",
    "\n",
    "part_files = sorted([f for f in glob.glob(os.path.join(csv_dir, \"part-*.csv\"))]) # Geting a sorted list of all part \n",
    "\n",
    "if not part_files: # raising an error if no part files are found to avoid writing an empty file\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\"No part files found!\")\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    with open(output_csv, \"w\") as outfile: # openning the output csv file in write mode\n",
    "        with open(part_files[0], \"r\") as firstfile: \n",
    "            header = firstfile.readline() # to read the header and first file's data\n",
    "            outfile.write(header)\n",
    "            for line in firstfile: \n",
    "                outfile.write(line)\n",
    "                \n",
    "        for fname in part_files[1:]:\n",
    "            with open(fname, \"r\") as infile:\n",
    "                next(infile)  # skips header as we already wrote it\n",
    "                for line in infile:\n",
    "                    outfile.write(line) # writing all remaining lines (data rows) from the first file to output\n",
    "    print(f\"Combined CSV written to: {output_csv}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "except IOError as e:  # to handle errors related to file reading/writing operations\n",
    "    print(f\"Error occurred while reading/writing files: {e}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "except Exception as e: # to handle any other unexpected exceptions\n",
    "    print(f\"Unexpected error: {e}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After merging, we clean up by deleting the original directory containing the multiple part files to save storage space and avoid clutter. This ensures we have one clean, unified csv file ready for further use."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 76,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
